The `dev test` (§3.8) human output for the deterministic, no-build paths. The CI entry
point never needs Live, Developer Mode, a daemon, or a GUI, and it never prompts. The
real build + runner paths (which need a node that can bundle esbuild) are covered by the
integration tests; here we pin the human error shapes that reproduce on any machine.

An operand that is neither a registered extension name nor a project path is `RK0001`
with the "register it, or pass a path" remedy — non-interactive, no prompt.

```
$ rackabel dev test does-not-exist
? 3
error: `does-not-exist` is not a registered extension or a project path [RK0001]
  --> does-not-exist
  help: register it (`rackabel dev register <path>`), or pass a path to a project directory that contains a rackabel.toml
(run `rackabel explain RK0001` for details)

```
